## Getting Started

### 1. Open in Protégé
If you use Protégé, just open `ontology/tbox/sro-labelled.ttl` to explore the structure.

### 2. Using Python
You can load the ontology into your code using the `rdflib` library:

```python
from rdflib import Graph

g = Graph()
g.parse("ontology/tbox/sro-labelled.ttl", format="turtle")
g.parse("ontology/abox/abox.ttl", format="turtle")

print(f"Successfully loaded {len(g)} data points.") 
